Rating: 4
I've made a variation of this recipe which was great; I think the biggest contributor to whether is is moist or dry is whether one uses western couscous (the little tiny sand like grains) or eastern couscous (the bigger, almost pasta like grains that look more like orzo)...the eastern couscous is, IMHO, way better for this sort of thing.

